# Feature Endpoint Rate Limiting

Authenticated feature endpoints should pair `AuthGuard` with `RateLimitGuard` and an endpoint-specific `@RateLimit(...)`.

```typescript
@RateLimit({ points: 30, duration: 60 })
@UseGuards(AuthGuard, RateLimitGuard)
@Post('create')
async create(...) { ... }
```

Public endpoints use IP-based rate limiting when exposed to untrusted callers. Webhooks, health, federation, bootstrap, and one-off confirmation links may use different guard/auth patterns, but should make the reason obvious in code or docs.

Use `developers/rate-limiting.md` for limit choices and `developers/VERIFICATION.md` for the invariant checklist.
